title: German team wins $5 million ANA Avatar XPrize in space-themed competition
summary: Germany’s Team NimbRo took home the $5 million grand prize in the ANA Avatar XPrize finals Nov. 5, after completing a test course that showed how remote-control robots could contribute to space exploration.

title: Psyche review finds institutional problems at JPL
summary: An independent review of problems that delayed the launch of NASA’s Psyche asteroid mission uncovered institutional issues at the Jet Propulsion Laboratory that led the agency to delay the launch of another mission being developed there.

title: Penultimate Antares 230+ to launch NG-18 with Antares 330 development underway
summary: Northrop Grumman is preparing to launch the second to last Antares 230+ rocket from Wallops Island, Virginia for the NG-18 mission to the International Space Station (ISS). Liftoff is set for 5:50 AM EST (10:50 UTC) on Sunday, Nov. 6.

title: Northrop Grumman ready for space station resupply mission
summary: Northrop Grumman is set to launch the penultimate flight of its current Antares rocket configuration — with Russian engines and a Ukrainian first stage structure — to begin a resupply mission Sunday delivering more than four tons of cargo to the International Space Station.

title: NASA, USAID Partnership Strengthens Global Development
summary: NASA and the U.S. Agency for International Development (USAID) signed an agreement Friday strengthening the collaboration between the two agencies, including efforts that advance the federal response to climate change.
